i look forward to chatting and also Ruth and Dottie and all my wonderful friends im putting this lil announcement update up so everyone can see what i have been up to and why i have  been a bit scarce as of late but i miss you guys so  much *big  tight hugs*   <br>
<br>
Hi everyone !!!<br>
 <br>
    I wanted to drop a line and send my hello's to everyone .<br>
Returning from a much needed holiday and time with Joe and the kids for Yule  and the  new year .<br>
  Things will be getting back to normal for me again soon but the going is bit slow and  daunting when looking at over 300+ emails put in my reply to box over the  past 4 weeks so bear with me  in my replies and pardon the mass mail catch up for  some of you who will get this more then  once .<br>
    I am over joyed that the nasty virus which plagued my computer and kept me offline in fear of passing it  is now gone .....(yay Norton 2002 it truly  rocks !!!)<br>
  Joe loaded &quot;Jezabe&quot; ( my computers name that sometimes testy  lil fiend that it is ) with a bunch more memory and got it running so awesome as well too!  <br>
   It has been a time of much relaxing and joy for me this past 3 weeks and i  so hated to see Joe board that plane again to go back to London again  ....after almost 4 years it  never gets easier those sad good-byes we have to share but oh the hello's  are always so wonderful .<br>
   As for my health i am  not feeling bad but i am  it seems so damn exhausted so much these days , my oncologist  has me scheduled for surgery  (the final one hopefully !!) and a trip to the plastic surgeon on the 29 of Jan.  ( new boobs maybe ? After all they have to match now !!   lol ahh for every cloud there is always a silver lining !!!!!<br>
     The most wonderful event was that Joe and i took the plunge and tied the note quite literally at our hand fasting on the solstice at the Yule circle  on the 21st  of Dec. !!!<br>
  It was a beautiful and romantic ceremony held on the lakefront as the winters chill rushed the circle , Rev Velvet and Donna were beautiful priestesses and lovely sisters to me and Joe and while the preparations were hectic , the dress was gorgeous ....a deep cranberry velvet with a black corset waist and bell sleeves that fell to the ground and a train to drag behind i felt like Cinderella indeed taking my princes hand !  We wrote our own vows and were warmed by all the wonderful folks , vampyre, pagan and full of wonderful energy who came !!  I had a crown of matching roses on my head and Cherie  ( my  lil one ) gave her mommy away , we jumped the room after exchanging pentacles and vows ( Joe looked so handsome and beautiful ) and enjoying  the rest of a lovely Yule circle . We then rushed  away for a brief but  wonderful honeymoon as we  watched an amazing thunderstorm from the high  rise window about the city  !!<br>
   I want everyone to know if i haven't gotten to your emails since about the mid of Dec, ( the computer virus then my holiday)  Know i will soon and i meant not to  have anyone think their mail isn't important to me . .<br>
To everyone  know you are in my thoughts and i hope to take part in the convos and get back on track as time and my health permit  .<br>
   Thank you all for your friendship and support .<br>
 <br>
 <br>
much affection,<br>
Sarya<br>
